  "Question": "<p>INMO '92 Question 9:</p> <blockquote> <p>Find <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_417\"><math alttext=\"n\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mi>n</mi></semantics></math></span> such that in a regular <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_418\"><math alttext=\"n\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mi>n</mi></semantics></math></span>-gon <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_419\"><math alttext=\"A_{1}A_{2}...A_{n}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>\u2062</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>\u2062</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span> we have <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_420\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{1}{A_{1}A_{2}}=\\frac{1}{A_{1}A_{3}}+\\frac{1}{A_{1}A_{4}}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>\u2062</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>\u2062</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>\u2062</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span></p> </blockquote> <p>I tried the following</p> <p>Assume it is inscribed in a circle.</p> <p>Then length of chord is <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_421\"><math alttext=\"2\\sin(\\theta)\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span> where <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_422\"><math alttext=\"\\theta\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mi>\u03b8</mi></semantics></math></span> is half the angle subtended at the center between consecutive points. So, <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_423\"><math alttext=\"\\theta=\\frac{180^{\\circ}}{n}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msup><mn>180</mn><mo>\u2218</mo></msup><mi>n</mi></mfrac></mrow></semantics></math></span>.</p> <p>Then we get <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_424\"><math alttext=\"\\csc(\\theta)=\\csc(2\\theta)+\\csc(3\\theta)\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>csc</mi><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mrow><mi>csc</mi><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03b8</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>+</mo><mrow><mi>csc</mi><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03b8</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span> Not sure quite how to proceed from there- using double and triple angle formulae doesn't seem to work</p>",
  "Title": "Finding <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_413\"><math alttext=\"n\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mi>n</mi></semantics></math></span> such that in a regular <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_414\"><math alttext=\"n\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mi>n</mi></semantics></math></span>-gon <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_415\"><math alttext=\"A_{1}A_{2}\\ldots A_{n}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>\u2062</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>\u2062</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow></semantics></math></span> we have <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_416\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{1}{A_{1}A_{2}}=\\frac{1}{A_{1}A_{3}}+\\frac{1}{A_{1}A_{4}}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>\u2062</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>\u2062</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>\u2062</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span>",
